propel.core

Class TryResult<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • propel.core.TryResult<T>

  • public final class TryResult<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    Class encapsulates a boolean value and a result. This is typically used to achieve returning two values from an operation where the operation may succeed or fail; on the first instance two values are returned (true and the result) but on the latter instance, only one (false). This is also a way of achieving C#'s 'out' keyword functionality in Java.
